Single center experience with a low volume priming cardiopulmonary bypass circuit for preventing blood transfusion in infants and small children. This retrospective study analyzed the current practice of blood transfusion-free open-heart surgery in 536 children weighing 5-20 kg undergoing surgery between 2004 and 2007. A miniaturized cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) circuit was used (priming volume 300 ml for the flow rate <1,500 ml/min